atching Each Other Improvise -- tUseful Lost Information Board -- tThe House With Too Many Doors -- tThe Auction To Get Less -- tThe Auction To Give Back -- tWe Should Design Our Waste -- tREST -- tThe Little Person Who Holds A Piece Of Wood -- t600 Steps -- tConviviality, Work, Leisure, and Retirement -- tABOUT THE CONSTRUCTLAB NETWORK -- tIMAGE CREDITS -- tACKNOWLEDGEMENTS -- tIMPRINT -- tPLAY0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aWe are all improvising. We are all making decisions. And we are all watching each other improvise. Together, we are improvising. Decisions become shared ones. We will have built this city together. Convivial Ground invites the reader to discover the work of the transdisciplinary European design-build network Constructlab piece by piece. Taking Ivan Illich’s understanding of conviviality as departure point, the essays, conversations, stories, and images in the book reflect on the specificities of collaborative practices as situated experiments, as well as on their possible roles in the creation of convivial societies. Exploring contemporary conditions of togetherness, learning, and working, the book is not a "how-to" guide, but an invitation to cooperatively write new convivial narratives.  aWir alle improvisieren. Wir alle treffen Entscheidungen. Und wir beobachten uns gegenseitig beim Improvisieren. Wir improvisieren gemeinsam. Entscheidungen werden gemeinsam getroffen. Diese Stadt werden wir gemeinsam gebaut haben. Convivial Ground lädt seine Leserschaft dazu ein, die Arbeit des transdisziplinären europäischen Entwurfs- und Baunetzwerks Constructlab schrittweise zu entdecken. Auf der Basis von Ivan Illichs Verständnis von Konvivialität reflektieren die Essays, Gespräche, Geschichten und Bilder in diesem Buch die Besonderheiten kollaborativer Praktiken als situationsbezogene Experimente ebenso wie ihre mögliche Rolle bei der Schaffung konvivialer Gesellschaften. Wenngleich die Publikation die zeitgenössischen Bedingungen von Gemeinschaft, des Lernens und Arbeitens erforscht, ist sie kein Handbuch, sondern eine Einladung, gemeinsam neue konviviale Narrative zu schreiben.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 4aIvan Illich. 4aKollaboration. 4aKonvivialität. 4adesign-build. 4agemeinsames Lernen. 4akollaborative Praxis. 7aARCHITECTURE / Individual Architects & Firms / General.2bisacsh1 aAcosta, Rebecca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBelrhaiti, Sara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChamekh, Laëtitia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aConstructlab, , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDehio, Johanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDevolder, Lucas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFehse, Mascha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLutz, Linus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMadison Fettingsmith, Noel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoritz, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPaquot, Thierry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPinto, Sofia Costa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPouzenc, Joanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPouzenc, Joanne, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRangel, Carla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRömer, Alex, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRömer, Alexander, econtributor.4ct